# Stratified Geometry and Topological Quantization in Causal Spaces

## Whitney Conditions, Obstruction Classes, and the Geometric Origin of Charge Quantization

---

**Abstract.** We develop a rigorous differential-geometric framework in which causal network structures are formalized as stratified manifolds. By introducing Whitney conditions, oriented stratifications, and topological obstruction classes, we establish a precise mapping from discrete causal hierarchies to continuous geometric quantities. The central result is that the fine-structure constant $\alpha$ is determined by the mean scalar curvature of the stratified space, topological obstruction classes, and inter-stratum torsion coupling, thereby providing a geometric origin for charge quantization. We further establish a rigorous proof of charge quantization via the integrality of the second Stiefel-Whitney class and connect the framework to Chern-Simons theory through the stratified analog of the level quantization condition.

**Keywords:** stratified spaces, Whitney conditions, Stiefel-Whitney classes, charge quantization, fine-structure constant, Chern-Simons theory, causal geometry

