## 6. Curvature-Torsion Coupling and the Fine-Structure Constant

### 6.1 Stratified Levi-Civita Connection and Curvature

**Definition 6.1** (Stratified Levi-Civita Connection). On each stratum $\mathcal{S}_k$, the **induced Levi-Civita connection** $\nabla^{(k)}$ is the unique torsion-free, metric-compatible connection on $T\mathcal{S}_k$.

**Definition 6.2** (Transverse Connection). At the boundary $\partial \mathcal{S}_k$, the **transverse connection** $\nabla^\perp$ describes the geometric transition from $\mathcal{S}_k$ to $\mathcal{S}_{k+1}$:
$$\nabla^\perp_X Y := \text{proj}_{\mathcal{S}_{k+1}}(\nabla^{(k+1)}_{\tilde{X}} \tilde{Y})|_{\mathcal{S}_k}$$
where $\tilde{X}, \tilde{Y}$ are controlled extensions.

**Definition 6.3** (Stratified Riemann Tensor). The Riemann curvature on stratum $\mathcal{S}_k$:
$$R^{(k)}(X,Y)Z = \nabla^{(k)}_X \nabla^{(k)}_Y Z - \nabla^{(k)}_Y \nabla^{(k)}_X Z - \nabla^{(k)}_{[X,Y]}Z.$$

### 6.2 Torsion at Stratum Boundaries

**Definition 6.4** (Stratified Torsion). The **generalized torsion** $T$ vanishes in stratum interiors (Levi-Civita property) but has boundary contributions:
$$T^a_{\ bc}(x) = \begin{cases} 0 & x \in \mathcal{S}_k^\circ \\ \frac{1}{2}(\Gamma^a_{bc} - \Gamma^a_{cb}) & x \in \partial \mathcal{S}_k \end{cases}$$
where $\Gamma$ are the connection coefficients of the transverse connection.

**Theorem 6.5** (Torsion-Second Fundamental Form Relation). At the boundary:
$$T^a_{\ bc}|_{\partial \mathcal{S}_k} = n^a (II_{bc} - II_{cb})$$
where $n^a$ is the unit normal and $II$ is the second fundamental form.

*Proof.* The second fundamental form measures the extrinsic curvature: $II_{bc} = \langle \nabla_{\partial_b} \partial_c, n \rangle$. The antisymmetric part $II_{bc} - II_{cb}$ measures the failure of the boundary to be totally geodesic, which is precisely the torsion of the transverse connection. $\square$

**Theorem 6.6** (Torsion Jump Condition). Across the boundary from $\mathcal{S}_k$ to $\mathcal{S}_{k+1}$:
$$\lim_{\epsilon \to 0^+} T(\partial \mathcal{S}_{k+1} - \epsilon) - \lim_{\epsilon \to 0^+} T(\partial \mathcal{S}_k + \epsilon) = \mathfrak{J}_{k+1,k}$$
where $\mathfrak{J}_{k+1,k}$ is the **geometric current** measuring the flux of torsion across the interface.

### 6.3 Derivation of the Fine-Structure Constant

**Definition 6.7** (Stratified Einstein-Hilbert Action). The gravitational action for the stratified space:
$$\mathcal{S}_{EH}[\mathcal{S}] = \sum_{k=0}^n \int_{\mathcal{S}_k} d^{d_k}x \sqrt{|g^{(k)}|} \left( R^{(k)} + \mathcal{L}_{bd}^{(k)} \right)$$